#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn50.1-12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn50.1-12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 50 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 50 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn50.1-12:0.2"
msgid "1. Gaṅgāpeyyālavagga "
msgstr "1. Abbreviated Texts on the Ganges "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 1–12. Balādisutta → pācīnaninnādisuttāni (bj)
msgctxt "sn50.1-12:0.3"
msgid "1–12. Balādisutta "
msgstr "1–12. Sloping East, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.249, sc1
msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, balāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five powers. "

msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.3"
msgid "Saddhābalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, satibalaṃ, samādhibalaṃ, paññābalaṃ—"
msgstr "The powers of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom. "

msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca balānīti. "
msgstr "These are the five powers. "

msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gaṅgā nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā; "
msgstr "The Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines to the east. "

msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.6"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañca balāni bhāvento pañca balāni bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant who develops and cultivates the five powers slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.7"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañca balāni bhāvento pañca balāni bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant who develops the five powers slant, slope, and incline to extinguishment? "

msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.8"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhābalaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ, "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant develops the powers of faith, "

msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.9"
msgid "vīriyabalaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "energy, "

msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.10"
msgid "satibalaṃ … "
msgstr "mindfulness, "

msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.11"
msgid "samādhibalaṃ … "
msgstr "immersion, "

msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.12"
msgid "paññābalaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ. "
msgstr "and wisdom, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go. "

msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.13"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañca balāni bhāvento pañca balāni bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant who develops and cultivates the five powers slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.14"
msgid "Dvādasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn50.1-12:1.15"
msgid "Gaṅgāpeyyālavaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr "(To be expanded for each of the different rivers as in SN 45.91–102.) "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.250, sc2
msgctxt "sn50.1-12:2.1"
msgid "Cha pācīnato ninnā, "
msgstr "Six on slanting to the east, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn50.1-12:2.2"
msgid "cha ninnā ca samuddato; "
msgstr "and six on slanting to the ocean; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn50.1-12:2.3"
msgid "Dvete cha dvādasa honti, "
msgstr "these two sixes make twelve, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn50.1-12:2.4"
msgid "vaggo tena pavuccatīti. "
msgstr "and that’s how this chapter is recited."

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
